Mission.Author: KingRaptor
Mission.Description: Ada aids an insurrection in their fight against the Empire's elite.
Mission.Name: Sunrise Episode 5E - Rebellion

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local units = GG.mission.FindUnitsInGroup("Dereg") for unitID in pairs(units) do local unitDefID = Spring.GetUnitDefID(unitID) local unitTeam = Spring.GetUnitTeam(unitID) GG.CAI.RemoveUnit(unitID, unitDefID, unitTeam) end
for i=1,3 do GG.CAI.SuspendAI(i, true) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(i, UnitDefNames.factorygunship.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(1, UnitDefNames.factoryamph.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(1, UnitDefNames.factorycloak.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(1, UnitDefNames.factoryveh.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(1, UnitDefNames.factoryhover.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(1, UnitDefNames.factoryjump.id, 0) if i ~= 1 then GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(1, UnitDefNames.factoryshield.id, 0) end if i ~= 2 then GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(1, UnitDefNames.factorytank.id, 0) GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(1, UnitDefNames.factoryplane.id, 0) end if i ~= 3 then GG.CAI.SetFactoryDefImportance(1, UnitDefNames.factoryspider.id, 0) end end

TriggerLogic.Name: Add Objective
TriggerLogic.Description: Scipio Astra of the Imperial Praetorian Guard has brought an army to crush a rebellion led by a comm named Athenion. Help Athenion out and potentially gain a new ally.
TriggerLogic.Title: Defeat the Imperials

TriggerLogic.Description: Don't let our new ally get killed.
TriggerLogic.Title: Protect Athenion

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: It is good to see you, Commander. Our foe has already established a strong presence here.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr: for i=2,3 do GG.CAI.SuspendAI(i, false) end

TriggerLogic.Message: Scipio Astra already has her tanks holding the valleys to the southeast. They will soon seek to dominate the skies as well.
Her auxiliaries are deploying spiderbots to the southwest. They will attempt to control the hills overlooking the field of battle.
Good luck, Commander. I think we'll both need it.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: GG.CAI.SuspendAI(1, false) local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada") Spring.SetUnitRulesParam(unitID, "facplop", 1, {inlos = true})

local x = 3600 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, 0) + 100 local z = -1200
for i=1,4 do local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("gunshipsupport", x, y, z, "s", 0) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, y, z) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {x, y, 1200}, 0) x = x + 64 end

TriggerLogic.Message: Imperial forces are advancing. We have Rapier gunships waiting to parry their thrust.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message: The Rapier is a good all-rounder that supports its allies against surface and air targets with disruptor missiles. Its chief weakness is its relative lack of speed.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local x = 3600 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, 0) + 100 local z = -1200
for i=1,4 do local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("armkam", x, y, z, "s", 0) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, y, z) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {x, y, 1200}, 0) x = x + 64 end

TriggerLogic.Message: To win this, we'll need speed and lethality. Let us ready some Banshee raider gunships, Ada.

The Banshee is a fast gunship best used in penetrating swarms to tear up enemy assets lacking adequate anti-air coverage. Its armor and firepower are decent, but nothing to write home about. Like many other raiders, it regenerates health when not in combat.

TriggerLogic.Name: Custom Action (Alternate)
TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local x = 3700 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, 0) + 100 local z = -1200
local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("blackdawn", x, y, z, "s", 0) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, y, z) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {x, y, 1200}, 0)

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: Ada, I've gotten you some Black Dawn strike gunships. They may give us the punch we need to win this.

TriggerLogic.Name: GUI Message (Persistent)
TriggerLogic.Message: The Black Dawn fires a volley of rockets that inflict heavy damage on anything in the target area. Its combination of speed, armor and firepower makes it perfect for hit-and-run attacks.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local x = 3664 local y = Spring.GetGroundHeight(x, 0) + 100 local z = -1200
for i=1,2 do local unitID = Spring.CreateUnit("gunshipaa", x, y, z, "s", 0) Spring.SetUnitPosition(unitID, x, y, z) Spring.GiveOrderToUnit(unitID, CMD.FIGHT, {x, y, 1200}, 0) x = x + 64 end

TriggerLogic.Message: The enemy's aerial capability is becoming more significant. We should deploy Trident anti-air gunships.
The Trident is essentially a flying Defender-like anti-air turret. It packs a good alpha strike against fixed-wing strikes, but its slow speed makes it a poor interceptor.
So, the Rebel of Tryphon enlists the aid of the wanted traitor and brigand, Ada Caedmon! Are you so completely lost to honor, dog?
Where was your honor when we stood off the Alans and Suevi alone, prefect? Does your dead Emperor lay claim to tribute without protection?
His will shall not be questioned by one such as you, traitor! Prepare for your destruction!
Let all heretics be cleansed in fire! I will revel in your destruction, scum!
Does she ever get tired of hearing her own fire and brimstone routine?
Strike down those who oppose His works! This is the judgement of the righteous!

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) Spring.SpawnCEG("gate", x, y, z) Spring.SpawnCEG("teleport_out", x, y, z) Spring.PlaySoundFile("sounds/misc/teleport.wav", 2.0, x, y, z, nil, nil, nil, "sfx") Spring.DestroyUnit(unitID, false, true)

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: You need to be more careful than that if we're going to win this, Ada.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr: local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("ScipioAstra") local _,_,_,x, y, z = Spring.GetUnitPosition(unitID, true) Spring.SpawnCEG("gate", x, y, z) Spring.SpawnCEG("teleport_out", x, y, z) Spring.PlaySoundFile("sounds/misc/teleport.wav", 2.0, x, y, z, nil, nil, nil, "sfx") Spring.DestroyUnit(unitID, false, true)

TriggerLogic.Message: Do not think you have won! I WILL CRUSH YOU YET, SCUM!

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Ada") GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true)
unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Athenion") GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true)

TriggerLogic.Message: AAAAAAAAARGH!
Take command of the rebel units, Ada. Let Athenion's death not be in vain.

TriggerLogic.CodeStr:
GG.CAI.SuspendAI(2, true) GG.CAI.SuspendAI(3, true)
local value = 0 if GG.mission.counters["Athenion Dead"] == 1 then value = 1 else local unitID = GG.mission.FindUnitInGroup("Athenion") GG.SetUnitInvulnerable(unitID, true) end
GG.mission.SendMissionVariables({ AthenionDead = value })

TriggerLogic.Message: Be wary of flak turrets and tanks, Ada. Try to avoid them if at all possible; else make them a priority target and keep your gunships spread out to minimize area-effect damage.
Flying close to enemy riot units is generally inadvisable, friend Ada.

TriggerLogic.Name: Convo Message
TriggerLogic.Message: For those who reject his word... only death awaits!
That's done. Now let us find the path forward.
